P(A \mid    X =x): = \frac{P(A \cap \{X=x \})}{P(     X=x)}
P( X=x) \neq 0
P(X =x) =0
P(A\mid    X =x): = \lim_{\epsilon \rightarrow 0} \frac{P(A \cap \{|X-x|< \epsilon\} )}{P(|X-x|< \epsilon)}
E(Y \mid    X =x): = \lim_{\epsilon \rightarrow 0} \frac{E(Y \times 1_{\{|X-x|< \epsilon\}})}{P(|X-x|< \epsilon)}.
f(x):=P(A \mid    X =x)
h(x):=E(Y \mid    X =x)
